WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.080 --> 00:00:00.980
Tadashi: Piece of red string,

00:00:00.980 --> 00:00:03.680
and, I threaded it through, a binder clip.

00:00:03.680 --> 00:00:05.840
The binder clip is carrying a passenger underneath.

00:00:06.020 --> 00:00:08.100
Let's say that this is a top of a mountain,

00:00:08.100 --> 00:00:10.100
and we are designing a funicular.

00:00:10.100 --> 00:00:14.460
I want to carry this passenger up to the top of the mountain, summit of the mountain.

00:00:14.460 --> 00:00:15.400
How can you do this?

00:00:15.400 --> 00:00:19.680
One solution is to just, uh, widen the string *cracks up* like this,

00:00:19.680 --> 00:00:22.000
and then make the whole thing go upward.

00:00:22.000 --> 00:00:24.500
But I don't think the engineers will accept this solution.

00:00:24.500 --> 00:00:29.820
So, what we do, is to keep those two strings absolutely parallel,

00:00:30.120 --> 00:00:30.980
no cheating,

00:00:31.380 --> 00:00:33.660
but then tug on them in alternating fashion.

00:00:33.660 --> 00:00:35.660
So tug, tug, tug, tug, and look!

00:00:36.020 --> 00:00:37.200
The clip...

00:00:37.760 --> 00:00:39.980
starts going up, spontaneously,

00:00:40.360 --> 00:00:42.360
toward the summit of the mountain.

00:00:42.420 --> 00:00:43.836
That's strange, right?

00:00:43.840 --> 00:00:44.480
Because...

00:00:44.680 --> 00:00:47.620
if you are just looking at the vicinity of my hands,

00:00:48.200 --> 00:00:50.420
what I'm doing is up and down, up and down,

00:00:50.420 --> 00:00:53.720
and it's a purely symmetric motion, up and down, up and down.

00:00:53.720 --> 00:00:55.320
So there's no directionality,

00:00:55.480 --> 00:00:57.360
and if anything, gravity's pointing downward.

00:00:57.520 --> 00:00:59.200
I mean this should keep coming down,

00:00:59.420 --> 00:01:03.280
but instead, by doing a completely symmetric up-and-down motion,

00:01:03.420 --> 00:01:06.200
I can take this thing upward,

00:01:06.560 --> 00:01:08.480
in a way that breaks the symmetry, yeah?

00:01:08.820 --> 00:01:10.820
Prefers to go up, and not come down.

00:01:11.360 --> 00:01:13.360
So, that is rather strange.

00:01:13.360 --> 00:01:16.920
And the wonderful thing about this is that it works even if you're not paying attention.

00:01:16.920 --> 00:01:18.420
You know, it's a really simple device,

00:01:18.540 --> 00:01:20.540
and even if you're, uh, not paying attention,

00:01:20.540 --> 00:01:24.120
and being distracted by, for example, my friend, uh, Brady there,

00:01:24.120 --> 00:01:26.000
I can just do this, and then...

00:01:27.280 --> 00:01:29.040
wait a minute, it's coming down, instead.

00:01:29.160 --> 00:01:30.800
So, and that's, that's wrong.

00:01:30.800 --> 00:01:32.540
So, I am just watching the [unintelligible].

00:01:32.860 --> 00:01:34.680
